# No Em Dash

Do not use the em dash character (`—`) in project-facing text content.

## In scope

- Documentation (`docs/**`, `README.md`, `AGENTS.md`)
- UI copy (labels, headings, buttons, placeholders, error messages)
- Code comments and JSDoc/TSDoc
- Commit messages and PR descriptions
- Marketing and onboarding copy

## Out of scope

- Third-party dependencies and generated vendor files
- Unicode characters required by external APIs or protocols

## Use instead

| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| `thing — explanation` | `thing: explanation` or `thing, explanation` |
| `First — second` in a list label | `First: second` |
| Missing table value `—` | `-`, `N/A`, or `None` |
| Parenthetical aside | Commas, parentheses, or a new sentence |

## Examples

```markdown
<!-- BAD -->
Every organization must configure a receiving wallet — the Stellar public key that receives payments.

<!-- GOOD -->
Every organization must configure a receiving wallet: the Stellar public key that receives payments.
```

```tsx
// BAD
<p>Payment completed — thank you.</p>

// GOOD
<p>Payment completed. Thank you.</p>
```

```markdown
<!-- BAD -->
- XLM — native Stellar lumens

<!-- GOOD -->
- XLM: native Stellar lumens
```

## When editing existing content

Replace em dashes as part of the change. Do not introduce new em dashes in generated copy.
